.TH "GOOBERS GATHER SIBLING CONTEXT" "1" "" "Goobers" "Goobers Manual"
.SH NAME
goobers gather-sibling-context \- load other open PRs as review evidence (a workflow stage)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgoobers gather-sibling-context\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
Usage: goobers gather-sibling-context [--no-cache] [--no-verdict-cache] [path]

Load the other open goober-authored PRs' touched files + state as
evidence for the holistic review (a workflow stage, follows
pr-select). Requires selectedNumber/selectedHead/selectedBase inputs
(Task.InputsFrom pr-select's own outputs). Sibling files are memoized
per head SHA under the instance scheduler dir, while check state is
always refreshed; --no-cache bypasses the file memo entirely (neither
read nor written) to force a fully fresh gather. Separately, this stage
also computes the selected PR's
reviewDigest and checks the PR's own most recent verdict comment for a
matching one (issue #523's verdict-level cache) — a match is emitted as
cachedVerdictJson, letting the runner skip the reviewer gate's LLM call
entirely; --no-verdict-cache skips that lookup, always forcing a fresh
review. Exit codes: 0 = context gathered (possibly empty — no siblings
is not an error), 1 = business error, 2 = usage/IO error.
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
goobers gather-sibling-context
.fi
